<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    Add warning that they should only use this page in the begining of the season, running generate will remove all existing games and add a new schedule
    <br>
    Add your generator options here
    <br>

    Add form to enter fields/court options, game times, start date, how many times each team will play each other, dates to exclude.

    <form action="generate" method="post">
      <strong>Court/ Field Name(s):</strong> <input type="text" name="field_names" placeholder="Names of fields/ courts">
        Please use a comma(,) to seperate the field/ court names.
        <br>
      <strong>Game Times:</strong> <input type="text" name="game_times" placeholder="Times to allow Games">
      Please use a comma(,) to seperate game times to allow.
      <br>
      <strong>Start Date:</strong> <input type="date" name="start_date" placeholder="Date to Start Games"><br>
      <strong>Game Day:</strong> <select type="collection" name="game_days" placeholder="Days of week to allow Games">
        <% @week_days.each do |key, val| %>
          <option value=<%= val %>>
            <%= key %>
          </option>
        <% end %>
      </select><br>
      <strong>Game Cycles:</strong> <input type="text" name="cycles" placeholder="How Many Times Each Team Will Meet"><br>
      <strong>Dates to Exclude:</strong> <input type="text" name="excluded_dates" placeholder="Dates to not have games "> Add dates in YYYY/MM/DD format<br><br>

      <input type="submit" value="Generate Games">
      <notice>Don't worry, you will be able to edit the games.</notice>
    </form>

  </div>
</div>
